          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurements of spontaneous fission events were",
                "performed using Chi-Nu array at LANSCE, Los Alamos"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 252Cf fission source was deposited over",
                "a hemispherical fission chamber.  One or two fission",
                "fragments may have triggered the fission chamber.",
                "Fixed threshold was applied to exclude alpha-particle",
                "interactions."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A Chi-Nu detector array consisting of 54 EJ309",
                "liquid scintillator detectors mounted at 15deg",
                "intervals along six arcs to form a hemispherical",
                "distribution of detectors was used for neutron",
                "detection. Each EJ309 detector was cylindrical, 17.78",
                "cm in diameter and 5.08 cm thick, coupled to a",
                "12.7-cm-diam photomultiplier tube Hamamatsu R4144.",
                "Only 42 detectors were used in the present experiment",
                "forming altogether 861 pairs of detectors at angles",
                "from 15deg to 180deg. The fission chamber with 252Cf",
                "source was placed in the center of the array."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight between fission fragment and",
                "neutron detection was used for neutron energy",
                "determination."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "CF252"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 252Cf spontaneous fission count rate",
